1
00:00:12,510 --> 00:00:17,690
[2009]

2
00:00:17,190 --> 00:00:17,870
Chuan,

3
00:00:20,420 --> 00:00:22,480
I want to discuss something with you.

4
00:00:25,070 --> 00:00:26,800
Where did you get this pocket watch

5
00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:27,800
and police badge?

6
00:00:28,280 --> 00:00:29,560
Is it issued by the SWAT team?

7
00:00:29,560 --> 00:00:31,740
It's a souvenir
from the provincial sniper competition.

8
00:00:31,740 --> 00:00:32,750
A souvenir?

9
00:00:33,350 --> 00:00:34,480
You got eliminated?

10
00:00:34,680 --> 00:00:36,280
Only the first place gets it.

11
00:00:36,970 --> 00:00:38,100
You got first place?

12
00:00:39,850 --> 00:00:41,520
First place only gets a souvenir?

13
00:00:41,520 --> 00:00:42,800
That's so stingy.

14
00:00:43,390 --> 00:00:44,650
You don't understand.

15
00:00:45,480 --> 00:00:47,010
Why wouldn't I understand?

16
00:00:47,760 --> 00:00:49,160
My birthday is coming up.

17
00:00:49,490 --> 00:00:50,750
Don't you understand?

18
00:00:50,750 --> 00:00:52,450
I'm cleaning it for you right now.

19
00:00:52,450 --> 00:00:53,510
Are you satisfied?

20
00:00:53,560 --> 00:00:55,620
I'm very satisfied. You know me best.

21
00:00:56,240 --> 00:00:56,750
You loot

22
00:00:57,250 --> 00:00:59,250
all my good stuff.

23
00:01:00,350 --> 00:01:01,850
What did you want to tell me?

24
00:01:01,850 --> 00:01:02,490
Yes.

25
00:01:06,610 --> 00:01:07,050
Chuan,

26
00:01:07,730 --> 00:01:09,130
I want to change my major.

27
00:01:09,700 --> 00:01:10,880
I think criminal investigation

28
00:01:10,880 --> 00:01:11,810
suits me better.

29
00:01:12,380 --> 00:01:13,180
Is Jiang Cheng

30
00:01:13,200 --> 00:01:14,280
really that good?

31
00:01:14,680 --> 00:01:16,080
I want to change my major.

32
00:01:16,690 --> 00:01:18,590
What does it have to do with Jiang Cheng?

33
00:01:18,590 --> 00:01:19,920
You applied to Jingzhou Police Academy

34
00:01:19,920 --> 00:01:20,950
just because of him.

35
00:01:20,950 --> 00:01:22,680
Jiang Cheng is a
criminal police officer now.

36
00:01:22,680 --> 00:01:23,700
And you can't hold back anymore.

37
00:01:23,700 --> 00:01:25,210
How is it because of him?

38
00:01:26,100 --> 00:01:27,770
Why can't it be because of you?

39
00:01:28,610 --> 00:01:30,210
Can't you be more confident?

40
00:01:30,640 --> 00:01:31,410
Besides,

41
00:01:31,700 --> 00:01:33,860
I've loved watching
Armed Reaction since I was a kid.

42
00:01:33,860 --> 00:01:35,060
That female cop

43
00:01:35,710 --> 00:01:36,479
is so cool!

44
00:01:38,550 --> 00:01:39,710
Being a female criminal cop

45
00:01:39,710 --> 00:01:41,120
is so hard, sister.

46
00:01:41,509 --> 00:01:42,150
Chuan,

47
00:01:42,509 --> 00:01:44,570
Mom and Dad already don't support me.

48
00:01:45,509 --> 00:01:47,240
If you don't support me either,

49
00:01:47,539 --> 00:01:50,210
I will be completely left alone.

50
00:01:50,240 --> 00:01:51,530
I'm so lonely.

51
00:01:51,550 --> 00:01:52,810
Do you know what facing loneliness

52
00:01:52,810 --> 00:01:54,090
means at my age?

53
00:01:54,340 --> 00:01:56,060
Loneliness is cruel.

54
00:01:56,289 --> 00:01:57,820
I need your support, Chuan.

55
00:01:57,990 --> 00:01:58,810
If I don't have you,

56
00:01:58,810 --> 00:02:00,620
I feel my life is hopeless.

57
00:02:00,640 --> 00:02:02,030
Alright, Jin.

58
00:02:02,790 --> 00:02:03,990
No matter what you do,

59
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:05,260
I will support you,

60
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:05,920
okay?

61
00:02:10,770 --> 00:02:11,330
Really?

62
00:02:11,710 --> 00:02:12,240
Yes.

63
00:02:12,590 --> 00:02:13,710
With me behind you,

64
00:02:14,200 --> 00:02:15,060
you can just...

65
00:02:16,540 --> 00:02:17,840
I can just...

66
00:02:19,500 --> 00:02:23,780
♪ Sister, be brave and walk forward ♪

67
00:02:24,340 --> 00:02:25,260
Don't look back!

68
00:02:25,260 --> 00:02:27,610
♪ Don't look back ♪

69
00:03:52,770 --> 00:03:58,310
[Sunsets Secrets Regrets]

70
00:03:58,670 --> 00:04:01,130
[Episode 9]

71
00:04:04,090 --> 00:04:05,550
Let's just have some beer.

72
00:04:05,810 --> 00:04:07,000
Let's play a game.

73
00:04:07,930 --> 00:04:08,740
What game?

74
00:04:09,190 --> 00:04:10,590
Let me ask you a question.

75
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:12,540
If you don't want to answer,

76
00:04:12,540 --> 00:04:13,380
you take a sip.

77
00:04:17,720 --> 00:04:18,370
Zhou Jin,

78
00:04:19,339 --> 00:04:20,660
are you mad at me?

79
00:04:20,730 --> 00:04:21,560
Cut the crap.

80
00:04:21,839 --> 00:04:23,100
Are you playing or not?

81
00:04:24,340 --> 00:04:24,900
Okay.

82
00:04:25,490 --> 00:04:26,130
Ask away.

83
00:04:29,930 --> 00:04:32,390
When did you
become a university professor?

84
00:04:37,420 --> 00:04:38,350
Three years ago.

85
00:04:39,440 --> 00:04:41,130
And when did you leave
the Provincial Bureau?

86
00:04:41,130 --> 00:04:42,130
About 5 years ago.

87
00:04:43,540 --> 00:04:45,460
Pretty convenient timing—

88
00:04:45,680 --> 00:04:47,280
showing up on our team
as a special consultant.

89
00:04:47,280 --> 00:04:48,810
That's not so simple, is it?

90
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:52,900
Zhou Jin,

91
00:04:54,490 --> 00:04:55,690
I am not your suspect.

92
00:04:57,420 --> 00:04:59,540
Starting with trivial,
irrelevant questions,

93
00:04:59,540 --> 00:05:00,470
using gestures

94
00:05:00,560 --> 00:05:02,050
to subtly stimulate responses,

95
00:05:02,050 --> 00:05:03,220
then building an association

96
00:05:03,220 --> 00:05:05,300
between those gestures
and telling the truth—

97
00:05:05,300 --> 00:05:07,490
that's one of the techniques
used in interrogation.

98
00:05:07,490 --> 00:05:08,950
Pavlovian conditioning.

99
00:05:09,900 --> 00:05:12,160
It's the first lesson in interrogation.

100
00:05:12,610 --> 00:05:13,250
Zhou Jin,

101
00:05:14,170 --> 00:05:15,230
don't do this to me.

102
00:05:24,900 --> 00:05:25,570
Sorry.

103
00:05:27,570 --> 00:05:28,900
Whatever you want to ask,

104
00:05:28,900 --> 00:05:29,900
I will answer you.

105
00:05:33,130 --> 00:05:33,780
Okay.

106
00:05:34,370 --> 00:05:35,970
Then I'll just ask directly.

107
00:05:36,610 --> 00:05:37,540
Do you like me?

108
00:05:38,490 --> 00:05:39,170
Yes, I do.

109
00:05:39,980 --> 00:05:41,570
Since when?

110
00:05:42,980 --> 00:05:44,180
Since our blind date.

111
00:05:44,670 --> 00:05:45,670
Why do you like me?

112
00:05:47,170 --> 00:05:48,430
With your conditions,

113
00:05:49,170 --> 00:05:51,300
you could easily find someone better.

114
00:05:51,780 --> 00:05:52,710
Someone like me—

115
00:05:53,650 --> 00:05:55,909
always busy with work, hardly ever home.

116
00:05:56,370 --> 00:05:58,050
You could've chosen someone

117
00:05:58,540 --> 00:05:59,659
gentler,

118
00:05:59,659 --> 00:06:00,570
prettier,

119
00:06:00,690 --> 00:06:02,050
and who could take better care of you.

120
00:06:02,050 --> 00:06:03,780
There's no one better than you.

121
00:06:16,780 --> 00:06:17,780
Did you marry me

122
00:06:18,610 --> 00:06:20,010
because you love me,

123
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:22,850
or was there some other reason?

124
00:06:25,300 --> 00:06:28,300
You've been involved in
the investigation all along.

125
00:06:28,460 --> 00:06:30,420
You already knew everything

126
00:06:30,780 --> 00:06:32,460
without me telling you about my brother,

127
00:06:32,460 --> 00:06:33,010
right?

128
00:06:35,780 --> 00:06:36,780
Who told you that?

129
00:06:37,100 --> 00:06:38,760
It doesn't matter who said it.

130
00:06:39,780 --> 00:06:41,810
I'm right, aren't I?

131
00:06:54,280 --> 00:06:57,810
5 years ago, the last time
you came into contact with that group,

132
00:06:58,180 --> 00:07:00,110
it was because of the lead you gave,

133
00:07:00,340 --> 00:07:01,100
wasn't it?

134
00:07:01,660 --> 00:07:02,300
Zhou Jin,

135
00:07:02,570 --> 00:07:03,420
it's unfair.

136
00:07:03,810 --> 00:07:05,170
This is the same question.

137
00:07:05,170 --> 00:07:07,010
You don't have to answer my question.

138
00:07:07,010 --> 00:07:08,140
Then keep drinking.

139
00:07:08,300 --> 00:07:09,300
But I have to ask.

140
00:07:42,250 --> 00:07:43,690
If it were anyone else,

141
00:07:44,150 --> 00:07:46,350
I would definitely try my best to ask him

142
00:07:46,610 --> 00:07:48,370
everything he knows.

143
00:07:49,860 --> 00:07:51,990
But when I found out that person is you,

144
00:07:53,690 --> 00:07:55,980
that was not the first thing I thought of.

145
00:07:56,680 --> 00:07:57,740
What I care about is

146
00:07:59,159 --> 00:07:59,870
exactly why

147
00:07:59,890 --> 00:08:01,620
you stayed by my side.

148
00:08:02,930 --> 00:08:04,100
Why have you

149
00:08:04,380 --> 00:08:06,060
never told me about this?

150
00:08:06,170 --> 00:08:07,770
What exactly are you hiding?

151
00:08:09,690 --> 00:08:10,370
Zhou Jin.

152
00:08:10,420 --> 00:08:11,350
Jiang Hansheng,

153
00:08:13,930 --> 00:08:15,490
please don't lie to me.

154
00:08:44,490 --> 00:08:45,820
You've heard of

155
00:08:46,650 --> 00:08:48,780
the Huaiguang serial murders, right?

156
00:08:49,960 --> 00:08:56,340
[1997]

157
00:08:55,410 --> 00:08:57,010
Back then in Huaiguang City,

158
00:08:57,580 --> 00:08:59,040
3 women were successively

159
00:08:59,490 --> 00:09:00,860
murdered in their own homes

160
00:09:00,860 --> 00:09:02,530
in just 3 short months,

161
00:09:04,060 --> 00:09:06,340
The most striking commonality
among the 3 cases

162
00:09:06,340 --> 00:09:07,610
was that the female victims

163
00:09:07,610 --> 00:09:09,670
were all wearing bright red dresses,

164
00:09:10,290 --> 00:09:12,620
lying on a bed scattered with rose petals.

165
00:09:14,220 --> 00:09:16,280
The fatal wound was a cut to the wrist.

166
00:09:16,860 --> 00:09:18,460
A bow was tied over the wound.

167
00:09:19,700 --> 00:09:20,940
Excessive blood loss

168
00:09:21,410 --> 00:09:22,610
caused their deaths.

169
00:09:23,010 --> 00:09:23,700
Prof was working

170
00:09:23,700 --> 00:09:25,700
at the Huaiguang CIB.

171
00:09:26,180 --> 00:09:27,820
Initially, his investigative approach

172
00:09:27,820 --> 00:09:29,750
focused heavily on the first case.

173
00:09:30,940 --> 00:09:32,170
He wanted to start from the beginning

174
00:09:32,170 --> 00:09:35,010
to quickly find the motive
behind the ritualistic killings.

175
00:09:35,010 --> 00:09:37,940
Despite deploying a large
police force for searches,

176
00:09:37,940 --> 00:09:38,580
checking

177
00:09:39,250 --> 00:09:40,710
all kinds of petty thieves

178
00:09:40,900 --> 00:09:42,960
and suspects with criminal records,

179
00:09:43,820 --> 00:09:45,620
there was no real breakthrough.

180
00:09:45,890 --> 00:09:47,740
Was there any narrowing
of the suspect pool?

181
00:09:47,740 --> 00:09:48,370
Hardly.

182
00:09:49,130 --> 00:09:50,250
The scene lacked

183
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:51,760
traceable evidence,

184
00:09:52,530 --> 00:09:54,990
and no usable fingerprints were collected.

185
00:09:55,610 --> 00:09:58,820
This person's counter-surveillance skills
are really strong.

186
00:09:58,820 --> 00:09:59,370
Did you make

187
00:09:59,370 --> 00:10:01,030
a criminal profiling report?

188
00:10:01,370 --> 00:10:02,010
Of course.

189
00:10:02,890 --> 00:10:04,650
But criminal profiling at the time

190
00:10:04,650 --> 00:10:05,770
was not yet mature enough

191
00:10:05,770 --> 00:10:08,170
to be directly applied in investigations.

192
00:10:08,460 --> 00:10:10,390
It didn't receive much attention.

193
00:10:11,770 --> 00:10:13,700
Just when the police were at a loss,

194
00:10:14,890 --> 00:10:16,750
someone claiming to be the killer

195
00:10:17,100 --> 00:10:18,160
turned himself in.

196
00:10:18,490 --> 00:10:19,550
Turned himself in?

197
00:10:22,910 --> 00:10:24,080
He was an accountant

198
00:10:24,710 --> 00:10:25,590
named Chen Li.

199
00:10:27,990 --> 00:10:29,620
The Huaiguang serial murder cases

200
00:10:29,620 --> 00:10:31,380
were able to be closed back then

201
00:10:31,640 --> 00:10:33,570
because Chen Li turned himself in.

202
00:10:34,140 --> 00:10:36,880
The police took Chen Li
to identify the crime scenes.

203
00:10:36,880 --> 00:10:38,330
He described his crime process

204
00:10:38,330 --> 00:10:39,560
very clearly.

205
00:10:40,370 --> 00:10:42,760
The details of his confession

206
00:10:43,130 --> 00:10:45,190
matched the crime scenes perfectly.

207
00:10:45,640 --> 00:10:46,900
What about the motive?

208
00:10:48,010 --> 00:10:50,040
He said he was dissatisfied with
his ex-wife's cheating

209
00:10:50,040 --> 00:10:52,700
and committed serial murders
to vent his anger.

210
00:10:53,530 --> 00:10:55,960
The details of the crime
were never disclosed.

211
00:10:55,960 --> 00:10:57,230
Only the killer would know

212
00:10:57,230 --> 00:10:58,220
the details of the crime best.

213
00:10:58,220 --> 00:10:59,680
Then he must be the killer.

214
00:11:01,210 --> 00:11:02,810
There was only one loophole.

215
00:11:03,040 --> 00:11:04,370
In the first case,

216
00:11:04,830 --> 00:11:06,430
the forensic doctor found

217
00:11:06,450 --> 00:11:08,380
sperm stains on the victim's body.

218
00:11:08,480 --> 00:11:09,840
DNA testing proved that

219
00:11:10,640 --> 00:11:12,170
it didn't belong to Chen Li.

220
00:11:12,960 --> 00:11:14,890
That's a major point of suspicion.

221
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:18,500
The explanation given at that time was

222
00:11:18,500 --> 00:11:20,060
that the victim had sex with other men

223
00:11:20,060 --> 00:11:21,650
before she was murdered.

224
00:11:23,760 --> 00:11:26,550
This suspect point wasn't
carefully investigated

225
00:11:26,550 --> 00:11:28,080
before the case was closed.

226
00:11:28,720 --> 00:11:30,090
That's too arbitrary.

227
00:11:31,530 --> 00:11:33,690
Your reaction is exactly
the same as Prof's.

228
00:11:33,690 --> 00:11:34,450
I heard

229
00:11:34,470 --> 00:11:36,600
he stormed into the captain's office,

230
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:38,300
almost flipping the desk,

231
00:11:38,510 --> 00:11:39,960
insisting the case couldn't be closed.

232
00:11:39,960 --> 00:11:40,920
I can totally picture

233
00:11:40,920 --> 00:11:42,580
what Prof must have been like.

234
00:11:43,100 --> 00:11:44,320
But the person involved

235
00:11:44,320 --> 00:11:45,250
didn't admit it.

236
00:11:48,570 --> 00:11:50,430
But there was nothing we could do.

237
00:11:50,880 --> 00:11:52,940
Chen Li showed up at the perfect time.

238
00:11:54,650 --> 00:11:55,790
Then what did Prof think

239
00:11:55,790 --> 00:11:57,390
the killer should look like?

240
00:11:59,250 --> 00:12:00,580
A local from Huaiguang,

241
00:12:01,010 --> 00:12:03,210
a middle-aged single man living alone,

242
00:12:03,440 --> 00:12:04,570
without a steady job

243
00:12:05,010 --> 00:12:06,740
but with some financial means,

244
00:12:07,520 --> 00:12:08,850
or someone persuasive,

245
00:12:09,570 --> 00:12:10,770
or with decent looks.

246
00:12:11,800 --> 00:12:12,560
Leaders,

247
00:12:13,690 --> 00:12:15,810
the times of the 3 murders

248
00:12:15,840 --> 00:12:17,440
show no particular pattern.

249
00:12:17,800 --> 00:12:20,640
One happened during a holiday,

250
00:12:21,070 --> 00:12:23,790
and two on weekdays.

251
00:12:24,050 --> 00:12:25,210
What does this mean?

252
00:12:25,680 --> 00:12:27,380
It means the killer isn't bound

253
00:12:27,380 --> 00:12:29,380
by an employer's attendance rules.

254
00:12:29,610 --> 00:12:30,300
Of course,

255
00:12:30,560 --> 00:12:31,760
the killer might also

256
00:12:31,760 --> 00:12:32,640
be unemployed.

257
00:12:33,990 --> 00:12:35,770
From the moment he chose his target

258
00:12:35,770 --> 00:12:37,860
to the act of killing,

259
00:12:37,890 --> 00:12:39,130
there were no signs of

260
00:12:39,150 --> 00:12:41,080
resistance or struggle.

261
00:12:41,670 --> 00:12:43,380
The victims had no

262
00:12:43,590 --> 00:12:44,470
binding marks

263
00:12:44,560 --> 00:12:45,670
or defensive injuries.

264
00:12:45,670 --> 00:12:47,170
We've examined the scenes,

265
00:12:47,170 --> 00:12:49,230
and the doors and windows are intact.

266
00:12:49,340 --> 00:12:50,600
What does this tell us?

267
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:51,540
It tells us

268
00:12:51,770 --> 00:12:53,730
the victims willingly

269
00:12:53,730 --> 00:12:55,340
brought the killer home.

270
00:12:55,650 --> 00:12:56,510
In other words,

271
00:12:56,860 --> 00:12:58,340
this man was very attractive

272
00:12:58,340 --> 00:12:59,770
in the eyes of women.

273
00:12:59,860 --> 00:13:01,520
So what makes him attractive?

274
00:13:01,700 --> 00:13:03,800
Nothing more than money, talent, or looks.

275
00:13:03,800 --> 00:13:04,350
Right?

276
00:13:04,890 --> 00:13:07,250
Chen Li is a petty accountant
at a small company,

277
00:13:07,250 --> 00:13:08,910
earning peanuts every month.

278
00:13:09,650 --> 00:13:11,940
He's plain-looking
and can't even speak clearly.

279
00:13:11,940 --> 00:13:13,250
He's unpopular at work,

280
00:13:13,250 --> 00:13:14,730
and his family is average.

281
00:13:14,730 --> 00:13:15,980
Chen Li

282
00:13:16,490 --> 00:13:19,410
fits none of the suspect's profiles.

283
00:13:19,610 --> 00:13:22,300
How could he be the killer?

284
00:13:23,100 --> 00:13:24,130
Impossible.

285
00:13:26,430 --> 00:13:28,070
In the Huaiguang series of cases,

286
00:13:28,070 --> 00:13:29,490
the most distinct feature

287
00:13:29,490 --> 00:13:31,250
is that when choosing targets,

288
00:13:31,580 --> 00:13:33,580
the killer has a specific tendency.

289
00:13:36,300 --> 00:13:37,730
Women in red dresses?

290
00:13:39,650 --> 00:13:40,650
That's crucial.

291
00:13:41,410 --> 00:13:43,100
It's an important criterion

292
00:13:43,150 --> 00:13:44,580
the killer uses
when selecting his targets,

293
00:13:44,580 --> 00:13:46,010
and it's the underlying motive

294
00:13:46,010 --> 00:13:47,530
running through
the entire serial murder cases.

295
00:13:47,530 --> 00:13:49,290
There was a woman in a red dress

296
00:13:49,700 --> 00:13:51,360
whom the killer hated deeply.

297
00:13:51,580 --> 00:13:52,410
He killed women

298
00:13:52,410 --> 00:13:53,820
who resembled her

299
00:13:53,840 --> 00:13:54,840
to vent his anger.

300
00:13:54,880 --> 00:13:55,960
Was it his wife?

301
00:14:01,490 --> 00:14:03,130
From what I know,

302
00:14:03,160 --> 00:14:04,350
that's about it.

303
00:14:05,250 --> 00:14:06,490
I don't really know

304
00:14:06,890 --> 00:14:08,200
anything else.

305
00:14:11,980 --> 00:14:13,580
Can I see your closet?

306
00:14:13,890 --> 00:14:14,460
Sure.

307
00:14:15,060 --> 00:14:15,610
This way.

308
00:14:22,220 --> 00:14:23,940
All my clothes are here.

309
00:14:30,100 --> 00:14:31,430
Do you wear red dresses?

310
00:14:33,270 --> 00:14:35,030
I never wear red clothes.

311
00:14:36,370 --> 00:14:38,300
Prof went to see Chen Li's ex-wife.

312
00:14:38,520 --> 00:14:41,320
She turned out to be
a traditional and plain woman.

313
00:14:41,530 --> 00:14:42,460
Her style of dress

314
00:14:42,460 --> 00:14:43,920
was almost conservative.

315
00:14:44,530 --> 00:14:46,250
She said she had never worn a red dress,

316
00:14:46,250 --> 00:14:47,650
let alone cheated on him.

317
00:14:48,010 --> 00:14:48,940
They divorced

318
00:14:48,940 --> 00:14:49,610
simply because

319
00:14:49,610 --> 00:14:51,810
of their incompatible personalities.

320
00:14:52,180 --> 00:14:54,530
Doesn't that prove he was lying?

321
00:14:54,940 --> 00:14:56,770
Couldn't the case be overturned?

322
00:14:56,770 --> 00:14:59,100
Prof didn't have time to submit the report

323
00:14:59,800 --> 00:15:00,930
before Chen Li died.

324
00:15:02,290 --> 00:15:03,520
He died of liver cancer

325
00:15:03,520 --> 00:15:04,590
in custody.

326
00:15:07,530 --> 00:15:08,730
Then I have an answer.

327
00:15:11,410 --> 00:15:12,250
It's a guess,

328
00:15:12,860 --> 00:15:13,660
not an answer.

329
00:15:14,650 --> 00:15:15,980
We all have our guesses.

330
00:15:16,720 --> 00:15:19,180
Chen Li might have taken the fall
for someone else.

331
00:15:19,180 --> 00:15:20,060
The killer

332
00:15:20,330 --> 00:15:22,060
could have told him all the details

333
00:15:22,060 --> 00:15:23,660
and made him turn himself in.

334
00:15:24,980 --> 00:15:26,380
Until there's evidence,

335
00:15:26,940 --> 00:15:29,270
speculation is always just speculation.

336
00:15:29,940 --> 00:15:31,000
After Chen Li died,

337
00:15:31,340 --> 00:15:32,410
there really haven't been

338
00:15:32,410 --> 00:15:33,610
any similar murders.

339
00:15:34,590 --> 00:15:35,920
And criminal profiling

340
00:15:36,180 --> 00:15:38,410
has always remained
at the theoretical stage.

341
00:15:38,410 --> 00:15:39,140
It has always

342
00:15:39,730 --> 00:15:42,390
only served as
a reference for investigations.

343
00:15:44,010 --> 00:15:45,200
Sometimes the truth will prove

344
00:15:45,200 --> 00:15:47,260
that the theory is completely wrong.

345
00:15:54,370 --> 00:15:55,180
Are you okay?

346
00:15:55,410 --> 00:15:56,210
What's wrong?

347
00:15:57,060 --> 00:15:57,650
I'm fine.

348
00:15:59,220 --> 00:16:01,550
But you haven't answered my question yet.

349
00:16:01,820 --> 00:16:03,080
What's the connection

350
00:16:03,100 --> 00:16:04,770
between the Huaiguang serial cases,

351
00:16:04,770 --> 00:16:06,430
the 8/17 Case, and my brother?

352
00:16:07,610 --> 00:16:09,010
Regarding the 8/17 Case,

353
00:16:09,080 --> 00:16:11,580
you only know about
your brother Zhou Chuan's sacrifice

354
00:16:11,580 --> 00:16:13,700
and that his service gun
went missing, right?

355
00:16:13,700 --> 00:16:14,580
I also know

356
00:16:15,580 --> 00:16:16,490
that the gang of criminals

357
00:16:16,490 --> 00:16:17,890
was caught by Leader Yao,

358
00:16:18,060 --> 00:16:19,590
and you were the informant.

359
00:16:21,460 --> 00:16:22,660
What you don't know is

360
00:16:23,100 --> 00:16:24,700
that before your brother died,

361
00:16:24,700 --> 00:16:26,060
he had a close-quarters fight

362
00:16:26,060 --> 00:16:27,700
with the 8/17 Case criminals.

363
00:16:27,700 --> 00:16:29,300
The police extracted bloodstains

364
00:16:29,300 --> 00:16:30,560
from his fingernails.

365
00:16:31,190 --> 00:16:32,630
The DNA of the bloodstains

366
00:16:32,630 --> 00:16:33,530
matched the DNA from the sperm stains

367
00:16:33,530 --> 00:16:35,340
in the Huaiguang Case

368
00:16:35,530 --> 00:16:36,530
from 20 years ago.

369
00:16:38,740 --> 00:16:39,590
Are they...

370
00:16:40,610 --> 00:16:42,010
Are they the same person?

371
00:16:42,130 --> 00:16:43,730
Because of this connection,

372
00:16:44,100 --> 00:16:44,650
and with the 8/17 Case

373
00:16:44,650 --> 00:16:46,580
making no progress for a long time,

374
00:16:46,650 --> 00:16:48,340
the Provincial Bureau decided

375
00:16:48,340 --> 00:16:50,130
to start with the Huaiguang Case

376
00:16:50,130 --> 00:16:52,460
to find this participant
in the 8/17 Case.

377
00:16:53,610 --> 00:16:55,610
But the Huaiguang Case
is also full of doubts,

378
00:16:55,610 --> 00:16:57,180
and they couldn't catch anyone at all.

379
00:16:57,180 --> 00:16:58,580
We start from the doubts.

380
00:16:58,940 --> 00:17:00,490
Based on the profile back then,

381
00:17:00,490 --> 00:17:01,980
Prof screened a lot of people.

382
00:17:01,980 --> 00:17:04,130
These people were all cleared of suspicion

383
00:17:04,130 --> 00:17:05,930
during further investigation.

384
00:17:07,740 --> 00:17:09,000
Was the profile wrong?

385
00:17:10,210 --> 00:17:11,099
You are right.

386
00:17:12,650 --> 00:17:14,450
After reopening the Huaiguang Case,

387
00:17:14,450 --> 00:17:16,300
Prof gave me all the evidence records

388
00:17:16,300 --> 00:17:17,780
collected by the police back then

389
00:17:17,780 --> 00:17:19,910
and asked me to issue a profile report.

390
00:17:20,369 --> 00:17:22,170
He was afraid his thoughts
would influence me,

391
00:17:22,170 --> 00:17:23,099
so he didn't tell me

392
00:17:23,099 --> 00:17:25,410
he had already written
a profile back then.

393
00:17:25,410 --> 00:17:27,609
Was there any difference in the result?

394
00:17:30,820 --> 00:17:31,370
Age.

395
00:17:32,650 --> 00:17:35,180
I don't think the killer
is a middle-aged man,

396
00:17:35,650 --> 00:17:36,650
but a young person

397
00:17:36,970 --> 00:17:39,130
between the ages of 18 and 23.

398
00:17:40,130 --> 00:17:41,990
The crime scenes, full of ritual,

399
00:17:42,270 --> 00:17:43,060
easily masked the original motive

400
00:17:43,060 --> 00:17:44,650
for the killings.

401
00:17:47,970 --> 00:17:48,540
Zhou Jin,

402
00:17:49,430 --> 00:17:50,630
are you looking at me?

403
00:17:53,540 --> 00:17:54,130
No.

404
00:17:54,890 --> 00:17:56,020
You are lying again.

405
00:18:07,650 --> 00:18:08,450
What's wrong?

406
00:18:08,890 --> 00:18:10,930
You got drunk on a bottle of cola?

407
00:18:11,890 --> 00:18:12,750
It wasn't cola,

408
00:18:13,170 --> 00:18:13,900
but seafood.

409
00:18:14,980 --> 00:18:16,380
I'm allergic to seafood.

410
00:18:17,860 --> 00:18:19,260
You're allergic to

411
00:18:19,690 --> 00:18:21,370
seafood-flavored instant noodles?

412
00:18:21,370 --> 00:18:22,170
Come on.

413
00:18:22,500 --> 00:18:22,970
I am.

414
00:18:23,410 --> 00:18:25,470
I just didn't get a chance to tell you.

415
00:18:30,540 --> 00:18:31,600
Do you have a fever?

416
00:18:33,650 --> 00:18:34,260
I'm fine.

417
00:18:35,210 --> 00:18:36,540
I'll be fine in a minute.

418
00:18:47,290 --> 00:18:47,940
Let's go.

419
00:18:51,210 --> 00:18:52,410
If you need anything,

420
00:18:52,410 --> 00:18:53,340
you must tell me.

421
00:18:58,890 --> 00:18:59,490
By the way,

422
00:19:00,020 --> 00:19:01,020
where were we?

423
00:19:02,780 --> 00:19:04,040
Criminal motivation.

424
00:19:04,610 --> 00:19:06,060
So you mean,

425
00:19:06,890 --> 00:19:08,060
no matter how fancy

426
00:19:08,060 --> 00:19:09,820
the killer arranged the scene,

427
00:19:10,130 --> 00:19:11,410
his original motivation

428
00:19:11,410 --> 00:19:12,870
was still sexual assault.

429
00:19:14,450 --> 00:19:16,260
A sex-driven crime.

430
00:19:18,930 --> 00:19:19,940
Since the killer

431
00:19:19,960 --> 00:19:22,410
could make the victim
take him home back then,

432
00:19:22,410 --> 00:19:23,260
it shows he had

433
00:19:23,260 --> 00:19:24,920
the ability to attract women.

434
00:19:26,100 --> 00:19:27,300
Logically speaking,

435
00:19:27,300 --> 00:19:28,370
he didn't lack women.

436
00:19:28,370 --> 00:19:29,390
There were 2 situations where

437
00:19:29,390 --> 00:19:31,390
he couldn't be satisfied sexually.

438
00:19:31,740 --> 00:19:32,430
First,

439
00:19:32,780 --> 00:19:34,310
he has sexual dysfunction.

440
00:19:34,860 --> 00:19:35,690
Second,

441
00:19:36,370 --> 00:19:38,210
the way he interacts with women

442
00:19:38,210 --> 00:19:40,270
was quite different from normal men.

443
00:19:41,240 --> 00:19:43,170
But the first has been ruled out.

444
00:19:43,500 --> 00:19:45,130
Because semen was extracted

445
00:19:45,260 --> 00:19:47,120
from the female corpse back then.

446
00:19:47,260 --> 00:19:48,370
So I think

447
00:19:48,860 --> 00:19:50,450
it should be the latter.

448
00:19:51,500 --> 00:19:52,460
The women took him home

449
00:19:52,460 --> 00:19:54,100
not necessarily because of his charm,

450
00:19:54,100 --> 00:19:55,340
but possibly because he triggered

451
00:19:55,340 --> 00:19:56,940
their protective instinct.

452
00:19:57,610 --> 00:19:59,180
Middle-aged men easily make women

453
00:19:59,180 --> 00:20:00,490
naturally defensive.

454
00:20:00,670 --> 00:20:02,890
But young men have an advantage
in this regard.

455
00:20:02,890 --> 00:20:03,650
Are you okay?

456
00:20:04,520 --> 00:20:05,650
We're almost there.

457
00:20:06,170 --> 00:20:07,610
Based on the trace inspection report,

458
00:20:07,610 --> 00:20:09,340
I conclude that he is a petite,

459
00:20:09,340 --> 00:20:10,300
and frail,

460
00:20:10,410 --> 00:20:12,860
young man who doesn't look very strong.

461
00:20:14,300 --> 00:20:15,300
When he appeared,

462
00:20:15,340 --> 00:20:17,000
he was extremely vulnerable.

463
00:20:18,740 --> 00:20:20,590
Among the 3 murder cases,

464
00:20:21,410 --> 00:20:24,010
the victims' ages
are showing an upward trend.

465
00:20:24,410 --> 00:20:25,690
This indicates that the killer

466
00:20:25,690 --> 00:20:27,970
prefers to choose more mature women.

467
00:20:28,890 --> 00:20:30,020
So I infer

468
00:20:30,460 --> 00:20:32,650
that the killer may not
have lacked romantic relationships,

469
00:20:32,650 --> 00:20:34,610
but rather had a problematic relationship
with his mother in his early years.

470
00:20:34,610 --> 00:20:36,090
He is from a single-parent family,

471
00:20:36,090 --> 00:20:37,690
raised solely by his mother,

472
00:20:37,860 --> 00:20:40,410
and has very serious
psychological problems.

473
00:20:40,410 --> 00:20:41,300
And it is very likely

474
00:20:41,300 --> 00:20:42,690
that he suffered betrayal,

475
00:20:42,690 --> 00:20:44,770
abandonment, and torture from his mother,

476
00:20:44,770 --> 00:20:46,540
leading to a twisted personality.

477
00:20:46,540 --> 00:20:48,070
While obsessed with women,

478
00:20:48,140 --> 00:20:49,600
he also deeply hates them.

479
00:21:00,860 --> 00:21:01,450
But

480
00:21:01,820 --> 00:21:04,080
15 years have passed since the incident.

481
00:21:04,690 --> 00:21:06,020
Even with a new profile,

482
00:21:06,820 --> 00:21:08,540
we couldn't catch the criminal

483
00:21:08,540 --> 00:21:09,780
in such a short time.

484
00:21:11,210 --> 00:21:12,410
But you have clues.

485
00:21:15,170 --> 00:21:16,970
The real murderer is not Chen Li,

486
00:21:17,300 --> 00:21:18,020
but Qi Yan.

487
00:21:19,540 --> 00:21:20,300
Qi Yan,

488
00:21:21,740 --> 00:21:24,000
the one who stabbed Cheng over ten times?

489
00:21:30,770 --> 00:21:31,960
How did you know him?

490
00:21:35,170 --> 00:21:37,410
Knowing the criminal's
personality weaknesses

491
00:21:37,410 --> 00:21:39,210
means knowing how to enrage him.

492
00:21:40,580 --> 00:21:41,860
I just threw out bait,

493
00:21:42,500 --> 00:21:43,300
and he took it.

494
00:21:43,650 --> 00:21:44,410
What bait?

495
00:21:47,740 --> 00:21:48,100
Me.

496
00:21:52,820 --> 00:21:54,020
He showed up in person

497
00:21:54,410 --> 00:21:55,540
to invite me over.

498
00:21:57,500 --> 00:21:58,170
And then?

499
00:21:59,260 --> 00:21:59,860
Then,

500
00:22:01,500 --> 00:22:02,500
he was arrested.

501
00:22:03,540 --> 00:22:04,600
It was a close call.

502
00:22:05,840 --> 00:22:06,780
Leader Yao and I

503
00:22:06,860 --> 00:22:08,260
had prepared in advance.

504
00:22:08,780 --> 00:22:10,110
He arrived just in time.

505
00:22:12,340 --> 00:22:13,860
You make it sound so easy.

506
00:22:16,450 --> 00:22:17,450
It was at that time

507
00:22:18,450 --> 00:22:19,650
Leader Yao led his men

508
00:22:20,170 --> 00:22:21,700
to take down their hideout.

509
00:22:23,210 --> 00:22:24,410
But looking at it now,

510
00:22:24,540 --> 00:22:25,270
it's obvious

511
00:22:26,060 --> 00:22:28,120
that he had a sizable gang behind him.

512
00:22:28,450 --> 00:22:29,310
Where's Qi Yan?

513
00:22:31,220 --> 00:22:31,850
He's dead.

514
00:22:34,260 --> 00:22:35,260
I guessed as much.

515
00:22:36,890 --> 00:22:38,540
At that time, as family members,

516
00:22:38,540 --> 00:22:39,690
they told us

517
00:22:40,380 --> 00:22:42,300
there were at least 2 attackers.

518
00:22:43,100 --> 00:22:44,630
One was brought to justice,

519
00:22:44,930 --> 00:22:45,660
and the other

520
00:22:46,450 --> 00:22:48,130
ran away with the gun.

521
00:22:49,370 --> 00:22:51,540
Then they told us this case

522
00:22:52,130 --> 00:22:54,130
would continue to be investigated.

523
00:22:55,060 --> 00:22:55,990
It has continued

524
00:22:56,060 --> 00:22:57,610
up to this day.

525
00:23:03,410 --> 00:23:04,120
Zhou Jin,

526
00:23:09,130 --> 00:23:10,330
we didn't find the gun

527
00:23:11,410 --> 00:23:12,500
or find out

528
00:23:13,060 --> 00:23:14,320
why your brother died.

529
00:23:15,880 --> 00:23:16,770
I'm sorry.

530
00:23:22,740 --> 00:23:24,470
What do you have to be sorry for?

531
00:23:25,970 --> 00:23:27,050
I actually didn't leave

532
00:23:27,050 --> 00:23:28,910
the CID of the Provincial Bureau.

533
00:23:29,060 --> 00:23:31,190
My identity as a university professor

534
00:23:31,210 --> 00:23:33,210
was just to hide my identity as a cop.

535
00:23:34,940 --> 00:23:36,020
I won't give up.

536
00:23:39,060 --> 00:23:39,780
So,

537
00:23:40,530 --> 00:23:42,060
you've been a cop all along.

538
00:23:49,410 --> 00:23:50,100
Thank you,

539
00:23:50,820 --> 00:23:51,750
Jiang Hansheng.

540
00:24:04,450 --> 00:24:05,740
Tell me more about it.

541
00:24:06,500 --> 00:24:07,300
At that time,

542
00:24:08,020 --> 00:24:09,350
how did you piss him off?

543
00:24:09,840 --> 00:24:11,170
What method did you use?

544
00:24:14,500 --> 00:24:15,900
I don't seem to remember.

545
00:24:17,170 --> 00:24:17,890
Then,

546
00:24:20,710 --> 00:24:22,770
what was his attitude when he saw you?

547
00:24:29,960 --> 00:24:31,420
Did he say anything to you?

548
00:24:32,100 --> 00:24:32,970
You were already

549
00:24:32,970 --> 00:24:34,370
in a life-or-death situation,

550
00:24:34,370 --> 00:24:35,970
he must have said something.

551
00:24:38,470 --> 00:24:39,870
I don't remember either.

552
00:24:40,780 --> 00:24:42,640
Why don't you remember anything?

553
00:24:43,300 --> 00:24:44,300
Then what do you

554
00:24:51,540 --> 00:24:52,450
remember?

555
00:25:02,650 --> 00:25:03,780
I remember Zhou Jin.

556
00:25:36,110 --> 00:25:37,770
The person who died 5 years ago

557
00:25:38,500 --> 00:25:39,340
was Mr. Yan.

558
00:25:40,380 --> 00:25:41,060
Mr. Yan?

559
00:25:42,370 --> 00:25:43,500
A respectful title.

560
00:25:44,130 --> 00:25:45,170
He was young,

561
00:25:45,300 --> 00:25:46,700
but highly influential.

562
00:25:47,740 --> 00:25:48,930
After he died,

563
00:25:49,820 --> 00:25:51,880
Old Scorpion laid low for a long time.

564
00:25:52,170 --> 00:25:53,130
Some say

565
00:25:53,970 --> 00:25:55,900
it was because he was traumatized.

566
00:25:55,930 --> 00:25:58,290
Others say it was because
he was short-handed

567
00:25:58,290 --> 00:25:59,690
and lost his confidence.

568
00:26:00,210 --> 00:26:01,740
You don't think so, Boss He?

569
00:26:03,930 --> 00:26:06,260
The 8/17 Case caused too much of a stir.

570
00:26:06,860 --> 00:26:08,210
Even Old Scorpion

571
00:26:08,820 --> 00:26:10,480
would have his reservations.

572
00:26:11,060 --> 00:26:11,580
Boss He,

573
00:26:12,130 --> 00:26:13,610
how did that Mr. Yan die?

574
00:26:13,920 --> 00:26:15,450
He was killed by the police.

575
00:26:15,740 --> 00:26:17,500
That's why Old Scorpion never let anyone

576
00:26:17,500 --> 00:26:19,130
touch the gun from 8/17 Case.

577
00:26:19,820 --> 00:26:20,780
Because Mr. Yan

578
00:26:22,010 --> 00:26:23,120
died that time.

579
00:26:25,100 --> 00:26:27,450
But Zhengtian just had to
steal it and use it.

580
00:26:27,450 --> 00:26:28,980
Isn't that courting death?

581
00:26:30,100 --> 00:26:30,610
Boss He,

582
00:26:31,290 --> 00:26:32,290
have you seen him?

583
00:26:34,820 --> 00:26:36,100
Do you mean Mr. Yan

584
00:26:36,520 --> 00:26:37,520
or Old Scorpion?

585
00:26:37,720 --> 00:26:39,520
You must have seen Old Scorpion.

586
00:26:41,410 --> 00:26:42,610
It's been years.

587
00:26:43,690 --> 00:26:45,020
After that case,

588
00:26:45,970 --> 00:26:47,630
Old Scorpion hid himself well

589
00:26:47,690 --> 00:26:49,150
and never showed up again.

590
00:26:52,020 --> 00:26:52,930
Then,

591
00:26:53,100 --> 00:26:54,160
what about  Mr. Yan?

592
00:26:55,060 --> 00:26:56,460
I only heard his stories,

593
00:26:57,160 --> 00:26:58,370
but never saw him.

594
00:27:02,380 --> 00:27:03,430
So mysterious.

595
00:27:05,690 --> 00:27:06,300
Boss He,

596
00:27:09,540 --> 00:27:10,740
everything is ready.

597
00:27:10,780 --> 00:27:11,300
Okay.

598
00:27:15,040 --> 00:27:15,610
Boss He.

599
00:27:15,860 --> 00:27:16,260
Come.

600
00:27:17,100 --> 00:27:17,930
Sit.

601
00:27:21,410 --> 00:27:22,690
Why aren't you eating?

602
00:27:24,280 --> 00:27:26,110
We have to put on a full show.

603
00:27:26,340 --> 00:27:27,600
We're coming out here camping.

604
00:27:27,600 --> 00:27:28,690
If your mood's off,

605
00:27:28,720 --> 00:27:29,850
it'll give you away.

606
00:27:30,180 --> 00:27:31,070
Come,

607
00:27:31,090 --> 00:27:31,690
have a drink.

608
00:27:31,690 --> 00:27:32,260
Come, Boss He.

609
00:27:32,260 --> 00:27:32,820
Come.

610
00:27:32,910 --> 00:27:33,440
Come.

611
00:27:36,450 --> 00:27:37,710
You guys eat and drink.

612
00:27:37,840 --> 00:27:39,770
Cheng, let's get down to business.

613
00:27:39,850 --> 00:27:40,330
Okay.

614
00:27:41,620 --> 00:27:42,270
Dahua.

615
00:27:45,060 --> 00:27:45,660
Everyone,

616
00:27:46,040 --> 00:27:47,640
hand over your phones first.

617
00:27:50,190 --> 00:27:51,840
No matter how many phones you brought,

618
00:27:51,840 --> 00:27:53,170
put them all in this box.

619
00:28:08,060 --> 00:28:09,170
From today on,

620
00:28:09,200 --> 00:28:10,450
everyone here is

621
00:28:10,450 --> 00:28:12,450
the backbone of Hengyun Logistics.

622
00:28:12,890 --> 00:28:14,890
This was personally appointed by Boss He

623
00:28:14,890 --> 00:28:16,450
after careful discussion
between him and me.

624
00:28:16,450 --> 00:28:18,130
After the power outage at the warehouse
a few days ago,

625
00:28:18,130 --> 00:28:19,210
I believe you all

626
00:28:19,240 --> 00:28:21,170
have heard something more or less.

627
00:28:21,820 --> 00:28:22,450
Indeed,

628
00:28:23,170 --> 00:28:25,170
there was a problem with that route.

629
00:28:25,650 --> 00:28:26,860
The reason why I brought you all

630
00:28:26,860 --> 00:28:27,890
to a place like this today

631
00:28:27,890 --> 00:28:29,130
is to tell you

632
00:28:29,410 --> 00:28:31,410
that we can't be so passive anymore.

633
00:28:32,130 --> 00:28:33,740
Boss He and I need your help

634
00:28:34,060 --> 00:28:35,460
to rebuild the new route.

635
00:28:35,610 --> 00:28:36,650
It must be fast

636
00:28:37,680 --> 00:28:38,480
and stable.

637
00:28:41,550 --> 00:28:42,680
This is what I think.

638
00:28:43,290 --> 00:28:45,570
We need to learn from Lai San's case.

639
00:28:45,970 --> 00:28:46,890
From now on,

640
00:28:47,060 --> 00:28:48,930
we will establish strict
organizational rules

641
00:28:48,930 --> 00:28:50,100
and structure.

642
00:28:50,540 --> 00:28:52,890
We will divide the personnel
into 4 levels.

643
00:28:52,890 --> 00:28:53,820
The top level is

644
00:28:54,050 --> 00:28:55,310
the regional manager—

645
00:28:55,650 --> 00:28:56,260
me.

646
00:29:01,690 --> 00:29:03,260
The regional manager
manages 6 store managers,

647
00:29:03,260 --> 00:29:04,930
which are the six of you.

648
00:29:05,690 --> 00:29:08,290
Each store manager
oversees a deputy manager.

649
00:29:08,860 --> 00:29:10,410
You guys decide

650
00:29:10,650 --> 00:29:12,920
the number of
frontline workers yourselves.

651
00:29:12,920 --> 00:29:13,730
Wait,

652
00:29:14,130 --> 00:29:15,590
this is a major reshuffle.

653
00:29:20,130 --> 00:29:21,060
Store managers?

654
00:29:21,370 --> 00:29:23,570
Why don't you just run a pyramid scheme?

655
00:29:27,130 --> 00:29:27,590
Yes,

656
00:29:28,060 --> 00:29:29,120
a major reshuffle.

657
00:29:29,220 --> 00:29:31,150
And we need to strengthen control.

658
00:29:31,880 --> 00:29:33,770
What if someone refuses to obey?

659
00:29:34,130 --> 00:29:36,170
The bottom-level staff can report
their superiors if they refuse to obey.

660
00:29:36,170 --> 00:29:37,780
I have the right
to dismiss store managers,

661
00:29:37,780 --> 00:29:38,930
but I don't have the power of appointment.

662
00:29:38,930 --> 00:29:41,060
The power of appointment
now belongs to Boss He.

663
00:29:41,060 --> 00:29:41,660
Of course,

664
00:29:42,020 --> 00:29:43,480
it will belong to everyone in the future.

665
00:29:43,480 --> 00:29:45,340
We respect the will of the people.

666
00:29:45,970 --> 00:29:48,690
If all 6 of you agree unanimously,

667
00:29:49,310 --> 00:29:50,180
you can also

668
00:29:50,210 --> 00:29:52,210
dismiss me as the regional manager.

669
00:29:54,970 --> 00:29:56,300
Are there any problems?

670
00:29:59,540 --> 00:30:01,400
Next, let's talk about the route.

671
00:30:01,890 --> 00:30:02,580
Xiao Mao!

672
00:30:03,260 --> 00:30:05,100
Cheng, the skewers will be ready soon.

673
00:30:05,100 --> 00:30:06,230
Bring us the phones.

674
00:30:14,510 --> 00:30:15,100
Boss He.

675
00:30:22,210 --> 00:30:23,500
Boss He's and my numbers are already

676
00:30:23,500 --> 00:30:24,860
saved on your phones.

677
00:30:25,130 --> 00:30:27,920
For the staff and routes
you're relatively familiar with,

678
00:30:27,920 --> 00:30:30,230
send them to me point-to-point
through this phone.

679
00:30:30,230 --> 00:30:31,970
I will consider them comprehensively.

680
00:30:31,970 --> 00:30:32,890
From now on,

681
00:30:33,130 --> 00:30:34,860
as long as it's about smuggling,

682
00:30:34,860 --> 00:30:37,120
we only communicate through this phone.

683
00:30:44,740 --> 00:30:45,340
Okay.

684
00:30:45,740 --> 00:30:47,000
Then I'll leave first.

685
00:30:47,500 --> 00:30:48,650
If you don't understand anything,

686
00:30:48,650 --> 00:30:49,690
you can ask Cheng.

687
00:30:53,650 --> 00:30:54,910
I didn't misjudge you.

688
00:30:55,060 --> 00:30:56,120
Thank you, Boss He.

689
00:30:57,820 --> 00:30:58,890
Take care, Boss He.

690
00:31:05,370 --> 00:31:07,370
Tonight we need to clarify a principle.

691
00:31:07,370 --> 00:31:09,500
Initially, we will only test the route

692
00:31:09,530 --> 00:31:10,860
and not move real goods.

693
00:31:12,370 --> 00:31:13,900
Do we need to be so cautious?

694
00:31:20,370 --> 00:31:22,020
We can't let the higher-ups know

695
00:31:22,020 --> 00:31:23,370
we're stashing anything,

696
00:31:23,370 --> 00:31:24,450
and we definitely can't let them know

697
00:31:24,450 --> 00:31:26,110
we're moving goods on our own.

698
00:31:26,310 --> 00:31:27,240
Don't you agree,

699
00:31:27,970 --> 00:31:28,650
Boss Li?

700
00:31:42,410 --> 00:31:43,170
Boss He,

701
00:31:43,540 --> 00:31:45,270
I've been thinking these days.

702
00:31:46,410 --> 00:31:47,130
About what?

703
00:31:48,300 --> 00:31:51,300
I'm worried Cheng
might try to step over you to rise up.

704
00:31:56,650 --> 00:31:58,410
Let's wait until he's done.

705
00:31:59,130 --> 00:32:01,130
Why are you in such a hurry this time?

706
00:32:02,940 --> 00:32:03,630
There might be a big shipment

707
00:32:03,630 --> 00:32:05,200
coming in recently.

708
00:32:05,780 --> 00:32:07,840
It'd be best if it could go through me.

709
00:32:14,670 --> 00:32:16,670
According to Zhao Xiaoyu's friend,

710
00:32:16,960 --> 00:32:19,480
she said that day Zhao Xiaoyu wanted to
go out for some fresh air

711
00:32:19,480 --> 00:32:21,100
and never returned to the bar.

712
00:32:21,100 --> 00:32:22,410
Later, when she texted her,

713
00:32:22,410 --> 00:32:23,860
Xiaoyu said she was a bit tired

714
00:32:23,860 --> 00:32:24,690
and went home.

715
00:32:25,590 --> 00:32:27,320
She went home with this person.

716
00:32:27,720 --> 00:32:29,580
Do we have a clear shot of his face?

717
00:32:30,770 --> 00:32:31,900
That's the problem.

718
00:32:32,380 --> 00:32:35,240
He seemed to be deliberately
avoiding the cameras.

719
00:32:35,300 --> 00:32:36,270
After coming out of the bar,

720
00:32:36,270 --> 00:32:37,990
he took Zhao Xiaoyu into the car.

721
00:32:37,990 --> 00:32:39,190
We didn't catch his face at all.

722
00:32:39,190 --> 00:32:40,850
And the license plate is fake.

723
00:32:42,300 --> 00:32:44,820
Did you check the cameras
near Zhao Xiaoyu's home?

724
00:32:44,820 --> 00:32:47,120
Lishui Residential Area
is an old residential area.

725
00:32:47,120 --> 00:32:49,060
There aren't many cameras to check.

726
00:32:49,060 --> 00:32:50,080
I checked them all,

727
00:32:50,080 --> 00:32:51,140
but found nothing.

728
00:32:51,450 --> 00:32:52,580
Play it for me again.

729
00:32:52,900 --> 00:32:53,250
Okay.

730
00:32:57,020 --> 00:32:59,680
You watch it first.
I need to make some medicine.

731
00:33:16,770 --> 00:33:18,030
Did you find anything?

732
00:33:19,410 --> 00:33:21,210
Can we track this license plate?

733
00:33:21,650 --> 00:33:22,020
Yes.

734
00:33:22,100 --> 00:33:23,160
That's easy. Here.

735
00:33:27,610 --> 00:33:30,740
Bin D2A523.

736
00:33:30,740 --> 00:33:31,170
Is that it?

737
00:33:31,170 --> 00:33:32,590
Bin D2A

738
00:33:32,930 --> 00:33:34,020
523.

739
00:33:35,540 --> 00:33:37,170
Zhao Ping, check this license plate

740
00:33:37,170 --> 00:33:39,430
and see if we can get the dashcam footage.

741
00:34:02,410 --> 00:34:03,610
You two, come with me.

742
00:34:07,210 --> 00:34:09,170
Xiaoyu,

743
00:34:10,010 --> 00:34:13,260
what exactly happened?

744
00:34:13,260 --> 00:34:15,300
My poor Xiaoyu.

745
00:34:15,929 --> 00:34:16,969
Who did this?

746
00:34:16,969 --> 00:34:18,489
Who did this?

747
00:34:18,489 --> 00:34:19,699
Xiaoyu!

748
00:34:27,179 --> 00:34:28,340
Xiaoyu!

749
00:34:31,340 --> 00:34:33,179
Look at Mom.

750
00:34:33,969 --> 00:34:35,860
Why did you turn out like this?

751
00:34:44,739 --> 00:34:45,409
I'm fine.

752
00:34:48,370 --> 00:34:49,900
Why don't you go back first?

753
00:34:50,659 --> 00:34:52,120
It's not good for the baby.

754
00:34:53,530 --> 00:34:54,489
We're fine.

755
00:35:01,930 --> 00:35:03,300
Xiaoyu!

756
00:35:06,700 --> 00:35:09,010
Why did you turn out like this?

757
00:35:10,930 --> 00:35:13,790
It's just like what happened to
my family back then.

758
00:35:17,310 --> 00:35:19,200
My parents were also

759
00:35:20,300 --> 00:35:21,380
crying inside.

760
00:35:26,530 --> 00:35:27,620
I was right here,

761
00:35:29,450 --> 00:35:30,580
in this exact place.

762
00:35:33,530 --> 00:35:35,090
I didn't even dare to go in

763
00:35:38,410 --> 00:35:39,810
and I didn't dare to look.

764
00:35:52,140 --> 00:35:53,220
Chuan,

765
00:35:53,940 --> 00:35:55,190
it's Mom.

766
00:35:56,090 --> 00:35:58,660
Open your eyes and look at me.

767
00:35:58,730 --> 00:36:05,810
[2012]

768
00:36:00,970 --> 00:36:01,530
Qiuyun.

769
00:36:02,320 --> 00:36:02,850
Qiuyun.

770
00:36:03,740 --> 00:36:06,090
How will we live without you?

771
00:36:17,780 --> 00:36:18,700
Jin.

772
00:37:25,620 --> 00:37:27,220
Once it's wrapped up inside,

773
00:37:27,890 --> 00:37:30,140
I'll talk to the victim's parents
about her situation.

774
00:37:30,140 --> 00:37:31,340
Don't worry about it.

775
00:37:34,580 --> 00:37:35,180
By the way,

776
00:37:35,700 --> 00:37:36,560
this afternoon

777
00:37:36,930 --> 00:37:39,370
the criminal investigation teams
from Ningyuan and Xin'gang

778
00:37:39,370 --> 00:37:40,260
are coming over.

779
00:37:40,260 --> 00:37:41,320
There's a lot to do,

780
00:37:41,660 --> 00:37:42,610
and I can't handle it all.

781
00:37:42,610 --> 00:37:43,470
Please help me.

782
00:37:48,900 --> 00:37:50,230
Xiaoyu!

783
00:37:50,570 --> 00:37:52,930
Why did you turn out like this?

784
00:37:52,930 --> 00:37:54,490
Who exactly did this?

785
00:37:58,530 --> 00:37:59,490
Dan,

786
00:38:03,420 --> 00:38:04,420
thank you.

787
00:38:35,220 --> 00:38:35,990
Mr. Wang,

788
00:38:36,010 --> 00:38:38,340
please help us out
and give us some advice.

789
00:38:39,970 --> 00:38:41,770
The great detective is here too?

790
00:38:44,050 --> 00:38:44,980
Long time no see.

791
00:38:46,050 --> 00:38:46,780
Mr. Liu.

792
00:38:46,860 --> 00:38:47,410
Hello.

793
00:38:47,430 --> 00:38:48,780
Leader, do you know each other?

794
00:38:48,780 --> 00:38:49,260
Yes.

795
00:38:49,260 --> 00:38:50,700
When I was first transferred to
the headquarters,

796
00:38:50,700 --> 00:38:52,010
we met a few times.

797
00:38:52,590 --> 00:38:55,320
Now I just hear stories.

798
00:38:53,020 --> 00:38:55,380
[Deputy Captain Liu Zishan, CID,
Binjiang Provincial Public Security Bureau]

799
00:38:56,450 --> 00:38:58,340
These are Captain Fang from Ninghai
and Captain Yu from Xingang.

800
00:38:58,340 --> 00:38:59,700
Hello, Professor Jiang.

801
00:38:59,700 --> 00:39:00,180
Hello.

802
00:39:00,490 --> 00:39:01,260
I've heard so much about you.

803
00:39:01,260 --> 00:39:02,520
I've read your papers.

804
00:39:03,070 --> 00:39:03,760
Leaders,

805
00:39:03,780 --> 00:39:04,450
let's go inside to talk.

806
00:39:04,450 --> 00:39:04,930
Okay.

807
00:39:15,180 --> 00:39:16,050
You're pretty impressive.

808
00:39:16,050 --> 00:39:17,050
Professor Jiang.

809
00:39:17,530 --> 00:39:18,010
Come on.

810
00:39:18,220 --> 00:39:19,280
Please take a seat.

811
00:39:25,370 --> 00:39:26,140
In the past,

812
00:39:26,170 --> 00:39:27,780
I used to hear Mr. Wang
talk about you all the time.

813
00:39:27,780 --> 00:39:29,530
I've read

814
00:39:29,550 --> 00:39:31,260
your research notes and case analyses.

815
00:39:31,260 --> 00:39:33,620
I didn't expect we'd get a chance
to work together.

816
00:39:33,620 --> 00:39:35,150
You're a real young talent.

817
00:39:35,690 --> 00:39:36,440
Thank you.

818
00:39:37,530 --> 00:39:39,060
How does it feel teaching

819
00:39:39,090 --> 00:39:40,570
at the Haizhou University
of Political Science and Law?

820
00:39:40,570 --> 00:39:42,300
Everything is going smoothly.

821
00:39:42,780 --> 00:39:43,890
You're leaving the front line.

822
00:39:43,890 --> 00:39:45,420
With all your great skills,

823
00:39:45,740 --> 00:39:48,010
it really feels like
you're being underutilized.

824
00:39:48,010 --> 00:39:49,140
I wouldn't say I'm underutilized.

825
00:39:49,140 --> 00:39:50,270
It's a very good job.

826
00:39:51,570 --> 00:39:52,180
Mr. Wang,

827
00:39:52,780 --> 00:39:55,220
A great teacher
produces a brilliant student.

828
00:39:55,220 --> 00:39:58,350
The brilliant student
will soon become a great teacher.

829
00:40:01,450 --> 00:40:02,820
Mr. Liu, let's begin.

830
00:40:03,010 --> 00:40:03,570
Okay.

831
00:40:04,660 --> 00:40:05,220
Zhou Jin!

832
00:40:05,740 --> 00:40:06,470
Let's begin.

833
00:40:14,310 --> 00:40:15,060
Leaders,

834
00:40:15,180 --> 00:40:15,980
and comrades,

835
00:40:16,060 --> 00:40:17,660
the materials for the 3 cases

836
00:40:17,690 --> 00:40:18,860
have been prepared

837
00:40:18,880 --> 00:40:20,030
and are at your disposal.

838
00:40:20,030 --> 00:40:21,840
I'll now give you an update

839
00:40:21,860 --> 00:40:23,280
on the latest progress
in the Zhao Xiaoyu case

840
00:40:23,280 --> 00:40:24,240
in Haizhou City.

841
00:40:27,960 --> 00:40:29,270
The deceased is Zhao Xiaoyu,

842
00:40:29,270 --> 00:40:30,580
female, 27 years old.

843
00:40:29,740 --> 00:40:32,710
[Zhao Xiaoyu Case in
Lishui Residential Area]

844
00:40:30,860 --> 00:40:33,220
On August 23, 2017,

845
00:40:33,220 --> 00:40:34,740
at 10:46 a.m.,

846
00:40:34,740 --> 00:40:35,940
we received a report.

847
00:40:36,090 --> 00:40:38,180
The victim died in her own home.

848
00:40:38,870 --> 00:40:39,610
The scene is located in

849
00:40:39,610 --> 00:40:42,670
Nancheng District,
Haizhou City, Binjiang Province.

850
00:41:06,850 --> 00:41:08,260
Let's first take a look
at the crime scene.

851
00:41:08,260 --> 00:41:10,060
Pay close attention to this car.

852
00:41:10,140 --> 00:41:11,490
Based on its position,

853
00:41:11,730 --> 00:41:13,210
if the dashcam

854
00:41:13,230 --> 00:41:14,490
was working properly,

855
00:41:14,620 --> 00:41:15,820
there's a high chance

856
00:41:15,820 --> 00:41:18,420
it captured a clear view
of the suspect's face.

857
00:41:19,140 --> 00:41:19,890
Don't worry.

858
00:41:19,890 --> 00:41:21,690
Once our Investigator Zhao Ping returns,

859
00:41:21,690 --> 00:41:23,150
everything will be clear.

860
00:41:24,490 --> 00:41:25,570
Okay, next let's take a look

861
00:41:25,570 --> 00:41:26,810
at the photos of the crime scene.

862
00:41:26,810 --> 00:41:29,040
[Zhao Xiaoyu Case in
Lishui Residential Area]

863
00:41:40,370 --> 00:41:41,170
